title: Frequently Asked Questions
content: All frequently asked questions about accessing TDP, submitting data, and bug reporting

title: FAQ: Are there restrictions governing where TDP can be used?
url: faq.html#Are there restrictions governing where TDP can be used?
content: The TANF Data Portal can be used from any computer in the US or US Territories

title: FAQ: Can multiple users on my team request access to TDP?
url: faq.html#Can multiple users on my team request access to TDP?
content: Yes. We're not limiting the number of users who can request access per TANF program

title: FAQ: Can I access TDP with a Login.gov account that I use for other services?
url: faq.html#Can I access TDP with a Login.gov account that I use for other services?
content: Yes, a variety of Federal organizations utilize Login.gov

title: FAQ: Can I access TDP with a Login.gov account that I use for other services?
url: faq.html#What should I do if a member of my team should no longer have access to TDP data?
content: If a member of your team has recently offboarded or no longer requires access to TDP & TANF data for your program, please contact us

title: FAQ: Do we need to change the way we prepare our files for submission?
url: faq.html#Do we need to change the way we prepare our files for submission?
content: Most TANF programs should not need to make changes to the way they prepare data. However, we do require that resubmissions be made with complete rather than partial data

title: FAQ: What are TDP's file update indicator requirements?
url: faq.html#What are TDP's file update indicator requirements?
content: The update indicator is an instruction to the system to add, update, or delete/replace records in the TDP database. 'D' is the only instruction the system accepts

title: FAQ: I'm receiving an 'Invalid Extension' error when I upload my data, how do I correct it?
url: faq.html#I'm receiving an Invalid Extension error, how do I correct it?
content: TDP requires data files to be submitted in recognizable format but some software tools produce files which lack this information

title: FAQ: How much data can I submit per day?
url: faq.html#How much data can I submit per day?
content: You’ll only be able to submit one quarter’s worth of data at a time, but you’re welcome to submit data for multiple quarters in sequence within the same TDP session

title: FAQ: Can I submit multiple quarters of data in a single file?
url: faq.html#Can I submit multiple quarters of data in a single file?
content: No. Each data file can only contain data associated with the specific quarter and fiscal year you've selected to upload to on the TDP Data Files page.

title: FAQ: Does “Closed Cases” mean the same thing as “Negative Cases”?
url: faq.html#Does “Closed Cases” mean the same thing as “Negative Cases”?
content: Yes, “Closed Cases” and “Negative Cases” both refer to Section 2 data

title: FAQ: I’m not familiar with Section 4 (Stratum) data—is it required?
url: faq.html#I’m not familiar with Section 4 (Stratum) data—is it required?
content: No. Section 4 is only for TANF or SSP programs that submit data on a sample of their caseload rather than universe data

title: FAQ: When can I expect to receive feedback on my submitted data?
url: faq.html#When can I expect to receive feedback on my submitted data?
content: In TDP you should receive an email from no-reply@tanfdata.acf.hhs.gov confirming that your data has been submitted shortly after submitting it

title: FAQ: Where can I report a bug or other issue with TDP?
url: faq.html#Where can I report a bug or other issue with TDP?
content: You can anonymously submit bug reports, feedback, and ideas for making TDP better on the Give Feedback page here on the Knowledge Center

title: FAQ: I have questions about the Program Integrity Review referenced in the Dear Colleague letter sent to TANF Administrators on August 27, 2025. Where can I find more information?
url: faq.html#I have questions about the Program Integrity Review referenced in the Dear Colleague letter sent to TANF Administrators on August 27, 2025. Where can I find more information?
content: ACF recognizes that TANF partners in states and territories may have questions regarding the scope, process, and expectations of the Program Integrity Review described in the Dear Colleague letter. Additional details—including specific data requirements
